@startuml Integrations_And_Sync

hide empty members
hide circle
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

title Integrations & Sync – Detailed Class Diagram

class ProviderConnection {
  +id: Integer <<PK>>
  +user_id: Integer <<FK→User>>
  +provider: String(50)
  +external_athlete_id: String(128)?
  +encrypted_access_token: Text?
  +encrypted_refresh_token: Text?
  +token_expires_at: DateTime?
  +scopes: JSONB?
  +status: String(30)
  +last_sync_at: DateTime?
  +last_error: Text?
  +created_at: DateTime
  +updated_at: DateTime
  --
  status: disconnected | connected | error
  <<unique: user_id + provider>>
}

class ProviderSyncState {
  +id: Integer <<PK>>
  +provider: String(50)
  +user_id: Integer <<FK→User>>
  +cursor: JSONB?
  +last_success: DateTime?
  +last_error: Text?
  +updated_at: DateTime
  +sync_status: String(20)
  +sync_progress: Integer
  +sync_total: Integer
  +sync_message: Text?
  --
  sync_status: idle | syncing | completed | failed
  <<unique: provider + user_id>>
}

class ProviderWebhookEvent {
  +id: Integer <<PK>>
  +provider: String(50)
  +event_key: String(255)
  +payload: JSONB
  +received_at: DateTime
  +processed_at: DateTime?
  +status: String(30)
  +last_error: Text?
  --
  status: received | processed | failed
  <<unique: provider + event_key>>
}

class IntegrationAuditLog {
  +id: Integer <<PK>>
  +user_id: Integer <<FK→User>>
  +provider: String(50)
  +action: String(50)
  +status: String(30)
  +message: Text?
  +created_at: DateTime
  --
  note: append-only audit trail for all
  connect/disconnect/sync actions
}

class HRVDaily {
  +id: Integer <<PK>>
  +user_id: Integer <<FK→User>>
  +source_provider: String(50)
  +external_record_id: String(128)?
  +record_date: Date
  +hrv_ms: Float
  +created_at: DateTime
  --
  <<unique: user_id + source_provider + record_date>>
}

class RHRDaily {
  +id: Integer <<PK>>
  +user_id: Integer <<FK→User>>
  +source_provider: String(50)
  +external_record_id: String(128)?
  +record_date: Date
  +resting_hr: Float
  +created_at: DateTime
  --
  <<unique: user_id + source_provider + record_date>>
}

class SleepSession {
  +id: Integer <<PK>>
  +user_id: Integer <<FK→User>>
  +source_provider: String(50)
  +external_record_id: String(128)
  +start_time: DateTime
  +end_time: DateTime
  +duration_seconds: Integer
  +quality_score: Float?
  +created_at: DateTime
  --
  <<unique: user_id + source_provider + external_record_id>>
}

class StressDaily {
  +id: Integer <<PK>>
  +user_id: Integer <<FK→User>>
  +source_provider: String(50)
  +external_record_id: String(128)?
  +record_date: Date
  +stress_score: Float
  +created_at: DateTime
  --
  <<unique: user_id + source_provider + record_date>>
}

ProviderConnection "1" -- "1" ProviderSyncState : tracks progress of

note right of ProviderConnection
  Stores encrypted OAuth tokens per provider.
  One row per user per provider.
  Separate from ProviderSyncState so that
  connection status is decoupled from sync progress.
end note

note right of ProviderSyncState
  cursor: JSONB stores provider-specific
  pagination token / watermark for
  resumable incremental sync.
  progress/total enable UI progress bars.
end note

note right of ProviderWebhookEvent
  Idempotency key = provider + event_key.
  Webhook is stored first, then processed
  async to avoid data loss on failures.
end note

note bottom of HRVDaily
  HRVDaily, RHRDaily, SleepSession, StressDaily
  all follow the same pattern:
  one row per day per user per provider,
  deduplicated by unique constraint.
end note

@enduml
